title: JoJos Circus
description:
Here are 39 episodes of the claymation series "JoJo's Circus" which airs on the Disney Channel. The series is aimed at preschool-kindergarten students and focuses on problem-solving and physical movement. The protagonist is a five- or six-year-old clown who has mini-adventures in and around the collection of circus tents in which she and her family live. Each show is about 11 minutes long, and each features a short song which encourages the audience to move along.

The shows were originally aired in a certain order, with two 11-minute shows being tied together and collectively assigned an episode number. Although no two shows so grouped contain related content, I have preserved that number system in the filenames of my .avi's. For instance, "S01.E04.p02" means Season 1, Episode 4, Part 2. The episodes were transferred from VHS to .avi, and I would say the quality is about 95% of what you would find on a DVD. A few episodes have about a quarter second of missing content where two files were joined together, and four of the 11-minute parts have a thin line (about the size of pencil lead) running along the top of the screen that is a different color from the rest of the display. Neither flaw detracts from the viewing experience.

The shows are cute without being sickly-sweet, and the content is engaging to little ones without being annoying for parents to watch repeatedly. The collection I have consists of the majority of of Season 1 and a few episodes from Season 2, and is incomplete. If you have recordings from any of the missing episodes or later seasons, message me and I would be happy to seed.
